Sorry I'm late#.#.#.# I know,       I know. I'm about 3 years late.# I said I was sorry.
As promised I will now teach you the ways of Ring Wizardry
I hope you're a good learner#.#.#. Because I'm not a very good teacher.
Every spell begins by conjuring a ring.# Like this.
Why don't you give it a shot.# Use your touchscreen or mouse to conjure a ring.
That's the right idea#, but stay focused.# Like this.
Almost#, but not quite!# Watch me and copy.
Close.# You almost had it.# Watch me again and try to mimic my actions.
Wow.# You actually did it!# I wasn't expecting that.
Um.# I didn't really prepare any further lessons#.#.#.# Guess I'll just wing it.
See that#, um#, pull tab thingy# on the side of the ring.# Try pulling it.
No#, I mean the smaller ring on the edge of the large ring. Pull that.
Good.# Notice how the chromatic spectrum shifted when you did that.
Now touch the center of the ring and swipe to the LEFT.
Whoops.# That was how you dissolve a ring you don't need anymore.
Just conjure up a new ring and I'll continue the lesson.
Now shift the chroma spectrum to RED with the pull tab thingy.
No, I said RED.# Once you've locked in a color you can't change it, so you'll have to start over.
Touch the center and swipe LEFT.
Wow.# Normally it takes weeks to master chromatic alteration.
I doubt you will be able to perform the next step so easily.
Once you have conjured a ring and chosen the chromatic spectrum, it is time to add a gesture.
Observe.# I will now show you a simple gesture.
Go ahead.# Just try and mimic that on your first day.# Good luck.# Ha ha!
Here,# I will show you again.# If only to humor you.
As I thought.# You'll need time to master this.# But, I will demostrate it again.
What?!# But how?!# I've never seen anyone create a working ring spell on their first day!
Be careful, this is a dangerous attack spell.
Touch the center and swipe RIGHT to try it out.
Touch the orbs along the outer ring to attack this old scarecrow.
This is a very simple attack spell. Different spells will have different effects.
Spells will eventually dissolve after they have been used up.
I'm glad you're picking this up so fast#, because# I#, sort of#, entered you into a tournament.
What?# Why are you looking at me like that?
Look.# There's a lot of pressure on us old wizards to put forward an apprentice each year.
I've missed the last 3 years running and I was getting a bit desperate.
Don't worry.# It'll be fine.# You'll probably be eliminated in the first round with a few minor hex burns. That's all.
And# one more thing.# Your first match begins in a few minutes so there's only enough time to learn one more spell.
Conjure up a new ring and shift the chroma spectrum to GREEN this time.
No, I said GREEN.# Once you've locked in a color you can't change it, so you'll have to start over.
Good.# Now I will demonstrate a popular green spell gesture.
Pay attention and repeat after me.
Lookie here#, I'll show you again.
Wow!# If my theory is correct# you might have a special gift for magic.
This spell shouldn't have been possible for a beginner to conjure.
Touch the center and swipe RIGHT to set it loose.
Press the outer orbs again to show that scarecrow who's boss!
That's all the time we have I'm afraid.
Keep an eye on your opponents#, you may be able to learn something from watching them.
Well#, we're about to be transported to the tournament.# Good luck!
How did you do that?# Have you already been trained?#
Wait.# I'm sensing something.#.#.# Yes.# I feel like I have taught you this all before in a parallel timeline.
Well then.# No point in hanging around here!# Off to the tournament we go!

Hi#. I'm Perry.# Get ready to avoid my spells.# This is gonna be awesome!# I just learned some new ones!
Wait#. I Won?# Yes!# Finally!# I knew I could do it if I put my mind to it!
*Sniff.# I lost in the first match again?# *Sniff.# Maybe next time.
Hey, do you like my outfit?# I made it myself y'know!
This is a long match!# Normally I'm out#, I mean, I've won by the third round.

Alright! I won!# Thanks for going easy on me.
GG.# It was an honor to duel with you.
Wow. You're pretty good!# How long have you been training?

You got me.# Well done kid.

Growl, growl#, growl!
Growl!
*Sad growl.
Raaa!
Let's see what you're made of two-leg.
You're crow-food!
Not bad for a mouse-brain.
You fight like a kitty-pet!
This is as far as you get.# I'm a pretty big deal around here you know.
You didn't really think you could defeat me, did you?
No.#.#. That's# Impossible.
Now for my secret technique.
I've been watching you.# You're good for a newcomer#, but you haven't earned my respect yet.

You're going to need to do better than that.
Come on!# Show me your true power!
I'm Ophelia.# You don't see many apprentices making it this far.# Especially not first timers.
You nearly got me!# I must be losing my touch.
Who did you say you were again?# You seem unusually talented for a beginner.
I'm starting to see how you made it this far.
Enguard knave!
You have fought well#, but lady victory was not by your side this day.
Ah, The bitter taste of defeat.# Fare thee well.
My honor is at stake!
Grunt, grunt#, grumble, squeak.
Gnarl!
Grumble.
Grunt grunt!
Blobby blobby blob blobby.
Blobby blob blob.
Blobby.
Blob blobby blob blob blobby blob blobby.
Greetings young wizard.#I am called Trentor.
Please understand I hold you in the highest respect.
You have bested me in battle.# I look forward to our next encounter.
You are strong for one so young.
That's a neat trick.# You'll have to show me it some day.
Grrrrrrr.# Why do they keep sending me such pathetic opponents.# I can smell your puniness.
Raaaar!# Go find me a worthy opponent.
Grrrrrr!# Next time you won't be so lucky human.# Get out of here before I get hungry.
I have no sight, yet you seem to be the one who is Blind
Roar!# Time to end this!
Hey, stranger.# Don't worry, I won't bite.# It's not that sort of battle.
Don't feel bad.# You got me pretty good a few times back there.
Wow kid!# You've got some impressive moves!
Ouch! I did not see that coming.

Wait till I tell the ocean about this!
Thanks for the match. I'll see you around I guess.
Aren't water spells just the best!
There's a lot of tough competition this year.# But I haven't lost a match so far.
It was real close.# But I'm still undefeated!
So, this is how I'm taken down.# By a simple beginner.
Now things are starting to get real interesting.
Hey, you're that new kid Aurelola told me about.# Good luck.
You certainly have skill.# But not enough to beat me.# Sorry about that.
I'll get you next time.
Aurelola was right.# You are a pretty good conjurer.
I foresee I world without smooth edges.# Behold, 8-bit superiority will conquer all.
Your defeat is but a taste of what's to come.# Glory to low resolution!
Enjoy your victory.# It's only a matter of time before the pixel-verse invades this realm.
Resistance is futile.# Pixelation is inevitable.
Croak!
Croak.
I croaked.
Ribbit ribbit.
Hello my pretty.# Are you certain you want to tangle with me?
Going so soon?# I wouldn't hear of it.# Why, my little party's just beginning!
You cursed brat! Look what you've done! I'm melting! Melting!
Double, double toil and trouble.
Greetings.# There are a great many ring spells within my pages.# How many do you know?
You'll need more study if you want to reach my level of knowledge.
I see now that there is more to great wizardry than knowledge alone.# Thank you.
It is written:# The more you read, the more your brain feeds.
Well look at what they're letting into the tournament nowadays.
That will teach you to underestimate creatures just because they are fluffy.
That was just a lucky break.
You smooth-skins think you own the world.# But really it's us fluffies.
You got a lot of nerve pulling a stunt like that.
I've been coming to this contest for hundreds of years and I've never seen anyone learn spells the way you do.# I'm a little scared to be honest.
Thanks kid.# I can't remember the last time I had such a good battle!
Your skills are Indeed superior to my own.# I will be watching your career with great interest.
I need to know more about this gift you seem to have.# How are you able to copy the spells?# Can you see into the ring void?
What does it look like?# Rays of light? Lazers? Sparkles?# I wish I could see what you see.
Howdy sugar.# You look young for a human.# But, then again#, I have trouble telling humans apart.
Nice try, but this match was decided before it began.
Beaten by another human.# I'm never gonna live this down.
Will you just stay down please!!# For your own good.
How about we cut to the chase and finish this!
Salutations.# Don't think I'll go easy on you just because you're human.# Not many of us make it this far you know.
Chin up.# You should be proud of what you've achieved.
No, this is not right.# I demand a rematch!
Let me give you a tip.# Your hair like,# really clashes with your outfit.
Do you even know the basics of dark magic?# How did you even get this far?
Oh, hello.# I'm Castle Hippopotamus.# But my friends call me#, er,# Castle Hippopotamus.
Hey wow!# I won again.# I seem to be really good at this for some reason?# Hey, but you're pretty good too.# Don't give up!
Woah!# You're really good at this circle magic stuff.# Can you teach me some spells sometime?
Sometimes it really helps if I imagine my name is Harry Pot#tamus instead.
Have you played 'Hexplore' before?# It's better than this game.# Well, that's just my opinion.# You should totally play it after.
Fun fact:# If you took the amount of hair you cut off in one year,# you could put it in a bowl and eat it like spaghetti.# if you're into that sort of thing.
Are you ready for Mr Cog's crash course in ring wizardry?
Lesson over.# I'll send you my bill.
I can see my teaching has done its trick.# I'll send you the bill.
Here's a technique I like to call# "Lights Out Time!"
Here's a helpful tip.# Spell projectiles hurt.# Avoid them if possible.
No time for talking. Lets do this.
If you see Scratch Cat around, tell him hi from his brother.
What?# Second best again...# Just like when Scratch chose my worthless brother to be their mascot.
You'll get nowhere with all that goodie, goodie magic.
Join me.# Embrace your negative side.
You wish to fight me?# You have chosen poorly.
Come back when you're ready for more pain.
Arrrg# It burns.# So this is what pain feels like.
I'd bite you, but it's against the rules.# But if I ever see you outside of the tournament# watch your back.
What up everyone!# It's yer boi 99 here.# About to lay the smack down on another victim live at Ring Wizard Jamboree!
Another easy win.# Hey don't forget to heart, favorite and follow me on InstaWiz.# Peace out.
Wait#, what?# But you're# a nobody?# Oh no, my subscribers.# Don't leave meee!# My life will be meaningless without followers.# Nooooooo.# I don't want to get a real job...
Did you see that?!# Thumbs up if you noticed my awesome dodging right there!
Hey, which of my spells has been your favourite so far? Leave a comment below about my fly moves.
Remember#, I'm approaching the big 3# point# 0# million subs.# Tell your grandma to sub to 99!
Let me take a minute to tell you about todays sponser Wiz-cream.# You know yer boi's down with the Wiz-cream daily.
Why follow your dreams when you can just follow me?!# You know it makes sense.
How unpleasent it is to see you, you snivelling coward!
I must posess all#, or I posses nothing.
How I lothe heroes.# Always getting in the way.
You couldn't beat a motley group of gnomes!
I'll win the old fashioned way, the tried and true way.# I'll cheat.
I'm so powerful!# I even impress myself.
A new challenger.# Welcome.
You've got a lot to learn before you beat me.# Try again kiddo.
What strength#, but don't forget there are many like you all over the world.
You are truly a formidable opponent.
Greetings my child.# May our battles outcome prove favorable.
Take heed when a wizards love of magic lies not in the heart but in the eyes.
Child#, beware of dark magic.# It's power will consume you if you allow it. Violent delights have violent ends.
Pride comes before destruction, and arrogance before a fall.
A gentle answer turns away wrath,# but a harsh word stirs up anger.
Even fools are thought to be wise if they keep silent.
Hmmm.# You don't see too many scavengers up here in the big leagues.# This ought to be fun.
You fought well#, but don't expect to beat a dragon any time soon.
Well, aren't you a cleverclaws.# Be on your way scavenger.
Fight me like a reptile!
You're becoming a real pain in the tail.
Twinkle Trousers greets you and hopes you will enjoy our battle.
Twinkle Trousers would like to thank you for such an enjoyable battle.
Twinkle Trousers congratulates you!# And Twinkle Trousers wishes you all the best in your final battle.
Twinkle Trousers is happy you made it this far.# Twinkle Trousers has not had this much fun in a long time.
Twinkle Trousers thinks you are a very good Ring Wizard.# How come Twinkle Trousers hasn't seen you before?
You must be that beginner I've been hearing so much about.# I'll make sure no one ever hears about you again.
Somehow I expected more from you.
No#, this isn't how I lose.# Not like this.# Not to you.# Noooooo!
Your spells are weak and childish. Just like you.
Come on.# Is that all you've got.
Would you believe this isn't even my final form?
You don't say much, do you.
Well well well!# Look at you!# Had I known you would be such an amazing student, I would have taught you sooner!
You are now officially the top Ring Wizard in the land.# Congratulations!
You've made me so proud.# All that hard work training has finally paid off, aye?
I sense an incredible amount of dark energy inside you.# There's no telling what evil you will do.# I'm sorry#, I must take you down now#, before you grow even more powerful.
Why?# Oh why cruel world?# You were supposed to be the chosen one!
No!# There must still be good in you.# Please# suppress this darkness# or the world is truly doomed!
Have you forgotton all I taught you?# Dark magic is never the answer.
You have a gift!# You could be an amazing force for good in the world.# Don't throw it all away!
If you continue down this path# forever will the darkness dominate you.
Mortal!# You challenge us?# The great Hexa and Accorus?# Prepare to be destroyed!
Ha!# Nice work Accorus!# Thanks Hexa.# You too!
You've got a lot of Spark kid!# We've decided to let you win!
It takes a lot more than a few spells to slay a two headed guardian.# Fool!
Hey Hexa,# are you sure we can win this one?# Of course, be quiet and keep fighting.
